23/12/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police announced on Wednesday (December 22nd) the bust of an international drug trafficking ring, arresting 29 people across the country.
Among those detained are alleged organisers of the so-called Frankfurt mafia criminal group, suspected of smuggling drugs to Austria and Germany.
During raids in restaurants and homes, police found large amounts of money and drugs.
About 350 police officers participated in the operation.
(Dnevnik - 23/12/10;
MIA, Sitel, Radio Free Europe, AFP - 22/12/10)
